Signs of the end.
What indicates that Russia is coming out of the crisis?
Economists have seen signs of Russia’s exit from the longest recession in twenty years.
According to Bloomberg analysts, the GDP of Russia is showing a positive dynamic - in the second quarter GDP decreased by 0.8% year-on-year.
This figure has been minimal since the beginning of 2015.
According to the latest data of Rosstat, the decline of the Russian economy in the second quarter slowed to 0.6%.
The Central Bank and the Ministry of Economic Development have also recently announced the stabilization of the situation.
Slow growth is ahead.
According to the experts of the Central Bank, the recession in the Russian economy has remained in the past.
“The index estimation of Russian GDP indicates that the recession has remained behind and ahead is the slow growth of the economy,” the Bank of Russia’s bulletin reads.
The modular estimate of GDP for the current quarter has been increased to 0.4%, the estimate for the fourth quarter is 0.5%.
According to the representative of the Ministry of Economic Development, during the second quarter, the decline of GDP of the Russian Federation stopped in the second quarter, amounting to 0.2%.
In the second quarter, seasonally adjusted GDP decreased by 0.2% to the previous quarter.
But during the quarter, the decline stopped: in April it amounted to 0.2%, and in May and June the change in GDP was within 0-0.15", - quotes the representative of MER RIA "Novosti".
The slowdown in the Russian economy over the past five quarters is a sign that the bottom has been crossed.
Among other markers pointing to signs of a revival of the national economy, Bloomberg calls the rising demand for electricity and rail transport a revival of business.
If you make an adjustment to the fact that the year is high, then it is clear that the dynamics in plus 1% of electricity consumption can be half caused by an additional working day.
Add to this a lower annual average temperature in the first quarter.
The next argument is the growth of freight transport, but here it is difficult to get accurate data, and plus-minus 0.5% of the half-yearly volume can also be explained by seasonality", - explains Kirill Yakovenko from ALOR BROKER.
However, there are other, more obvious signs of stabilization of the Russian economy.
For example, a reduction in price pressure.
In July, the consumer price index was 7.2% compared to 15.6% in the same month of last year.
Moreover, in the last two weeks, Rosstat has recorded deflation.
Prices in Russia have fallen for the first time in five years.
If you look at the price dynamics of the ruble, which, although showed strong fluctuations at the beginning of the year, according to the results of August has strengthened by 12% since the beginning of the year.
This is also one of the signs of recovery, which should be followed by indicators from the real sector of the economy," Yakovenko stressed.
In addition, since April, there has been an increase in the volume of industrial production in Russia.
In June, the figure increased by 1.7%.
The rate of decline in foreign trade turnover slows from -32.8% in January 2016 to -20.7% in May.
The positive momentum is also demonstrated by the situation in the labour market, where the unemployment rate has fallen to 5.4%.
Below it was only in September 2015 (5.2%).
Despite the prosperous situation in the labour market, the question of the real disposable income of the population leaves to desire the best.
In annual terms, the figure decreases by 4.8%.
This factor could hamper the recovery of the economy, as household spending contributes a considerable amount to GDP.
As a rule, in the structure of the economy their share exceeds 50%.
In addition to low consumer activity, the Bank of Russia’s tough policy can also be called as risk factors for economic growth.
The regulator keeps the bet at 10.5%, which does not have the best effect on the real sector.
A negative factor is also the insufficient level of investment, which inhibits the development of industrial potential.
But in general, it can be assumed that by the end of the year, the rate of decline of the Russian economy will slow down to -0.5% versus -3.7% in 2015," said Irina Rogova, analyst at Forex Club.
