The Armed Forces of the Black Sea Fleet carried out the development of anti-submarine and diversion defenses in the Black Sea waters.
About this RIA Novosti reported the representative of the press service of the Ministry of Defense of the Navy Igor Dygalo.
The training was conducted in the framework of the first stage of exercises on special types of operations of the navy forces.
"Military personnel of the anti-submarine-division units have deployed the anti-submarine-division defense of the naval force base on the coastline and adjacent seawater of the Black Sea," Digalo said.
The exercises involved about 400 soldiers, more than 10 units of combat equipment, including Mi-8 and Ka-27 helicopters, anti-diversion boats "Grachonok" and patrol fast-moving boats "Raptor".
In the course of maneuvers, the force of the fire mined ships using hydroacoustic means detected conditional diversion groups and reflected the attack of "submarine divers" from the side of the sea at the point of base of the forces of the CF.
From the Ka-27 helicopter landed a landing and storm group, which blocked and destroyed the divergents of the conditional enemy.
After that, the Black Sea Fleet troopers went out to sea in search of mines.
Dygalo said that "the Black Sea Fleet exercises are carried out in accordance with the plan of preparation and conduct of the upcoming command and staff exercise "Caucasus-2016" and the Navy training plan."
From 18 to 30 July, Ukraine and the United States conducted joint military exercises of the Sea Breeze fleets 2016 in the Black Sea.
In total, about 4,000 people from 16 countries took part in the maneuvers.
The marine component involved more than 25 ships, boats and supply vessels of the United States, Turkey, Romania and Ukraine.
