Miguly was found guilty of the crimes provided for in articles 286 ("Excession of powers"), 285.1 ("Expenditure of budgetary resources") and 285 ("Abuse of official powers") of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation.
The investigation found that in December 2008, the official provided his familiar land plot in the village of Muhinka in violation of the established land law procedure.
In 2006, he illegally issued a decree on the acquisition of the city’s highway bridge through the Chigiri River, at an overpriced price without competitive procedures and the conclusion of a municipal contract, Interfax clarifies.
In addition, during the period from 2007 to 2010, Migul, in the interest of the commercial organization under his control, changed the terms of payments under the contract for the purchase and sale of a lease of land, which was granted for the construction of housing, and also exempted the company from the rent.
As a result, the budget of the region did not reach more than 5 million rubles, and the urban penalty is about 21 million rubles.
On August 4, it became known that the former mayor, who was in custody on suspicion of corruption, and applied for a parliamentary term, did not provide in the election signatures for participation in the elections in the State Duma and was removed from the pre-election race.
Migulya was arrested in May 2015 in the Lipetsk region and placed in the SISO.
