Owners of messaging and postal services must identify users and remove the prohibited information - such is the brief content of the bill developed by the Media-Communication Union (MKS), which brings together the "biggest Russian operators" (communications).
Employees of three companies - members of the union confirmed that such a project is being discussed.
In early autumn, it should be presented to the working group under the leadership of the first Deputy Prime Minister Igor Shuvalov, says the interlocutor of "Vedomosti" at the ISS.
We are talking about amendments to the communications and media laws.
They provide that any "organizer of the dissemination of information on the Internet, which provides the possibility of exchange of electronic communications", is obliged to identify users on the basis of the information contained in the databases of the operators of communication, by concluding contracts with them in advance.
“Immediately block messages or publications that contain information disseminated in violation of the requirements of Russian law.”
Otherwise, operators have the right to restrict access to the service at Roskomnadzor’s decision.
