FAS fined Google almost half a billion rubles
The reason was a violation of competition in the mobile app market.
The anti-monopoly trial was initiated on the initiative of Yandex.
The Russian company claimed that Google provides smartphone manufacturers with access to Android components under conditions that prohibited the pre-installation of apps from other developers, in particular from Yandex.
The FAS found confirmation of these claims and found that the company abused the dominant position in the market and imposed on mobile device manufacturers the installation along with the Google Play store of other apps.
According to the results of the check, the Federal Antimonopoly Service has decided to punish Google, Deputy Head of the FAS Alexey Dotsenko said.
The fine must be paid within 60 days of the entry into force of the decree.
The FAS concluded that the law on competition protection must be respected by all companies, including transnational corporations.
In turn, Google intends to first study the solution and only then determine with further actions: to execute it or to challenge it.
The Federal Antimonopoly Service recognized the company as a violation of the competition law back in September last year and prescribed to adjust the contracts until December 18.
However, Google did not agree to this.
Since then, the company and the department have been conducting legal proceedings.
The FAS noted that, despite the fine, the possibility of a world agreement is being discussed with Google.
This measure will not lead to anything.
This view was expressed by the leading analyst of Mobile research group Eldar Murtazin.
Murtazin also noted that the fine will not affect neither the users nor the competitiveness of the corporation.
